ide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice de Norfolk was born about 1266, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Ralph De Avenel. She died after 1300."},"et":{"about 1266–after 1300":"umbes 1266–pärast 1300","1262–1300":"1262–1300","1279–1340":"1279–1340","1266–1300":"1266–1300","1279":"1279","before 1300":"enne 1300","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","about 1279":"umbes 1279","1340":"1340","about 1266":"umbes 1266","1262":"1262","after 1300":"pärast 1300","Norfork,  England, United Kingdom":"England","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1266–after 1300":"noin 1266–1300 jälkeen","1262–1300":"1262–1300","1279–1340":"1279–1340","1266–1300":"1266–1300","1279":"1279","before 1300":"ennen vuotta 1300","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","about 1279":"noin 1279","1340":"1340","about 1266":"noin 1266","1262":"1262","after 1300":"1300 jälkeen","Norfork,  England, United Kingdom":"England","Norfolk, England, United Kingdom":"Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1266–after 1300":"environ 1266–après 1300","1262–1300":"1262–1300","1279–1340":"1279–1340","1266–1300":"1266–1300","1279":"1279","before 1300":"avant 1300","1300":"1300","1266":"1266","about 1279":"environ 1279","1340":"1340","about 1266":